Package: mlemur
Type: Package
Title: MLE MUtatution Rate Calculator
Version: 0.9.6.2
Date: 2023-01-10
Authors@R: c(person("Krystian", "Lazowski", role = c("aut", "cre"),
	           email = "lazowski.krystian@outlook.com", comment = c(ORCID="0000-0001-5163-7026")),
	           person("Qi", "Zheng", role = "ctb", comment = "The code for simulating fluctuation experiments (rluria),
	           calculating some auxiliary sequences (aux_seq), the values of probability mass function
	           (prob_ld, prob_ld_deriv, prob_b0), maximum likelihood estimates (optim_m), confidence intervals (root_m),
	           p-values (combo_optim_m), and number of mutations (p0, jones.median), was inspired by the frameworks
	           developed by Qi Zheng and implemented in rSalvador. The functions are referenced in documentation."))
Author: Krystian Lazowski [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5163-7026>),
        Qi Zheng [ctb]
Maintainer: Krystian Lazowski <klazowski@ibb.waw.pl>
Description: A tool for calculating maximum likelihood-based mutation rates,
  confidence intervals, and P values. Offers graphical user interface built with shiny.
  Based on rSalvador by Qi Zheng <https://github.com/eeeeeric/rSalvador>.
License: GPL (>= 2)
SystemRequirements: gmp (>=6.2.1), mpfr (>=4.1.0)
SystemRequirementsNote: 'MPFR' (MP Floating-Point Reliable Library,
                        https://www.mpfr.org/) and 'GMP' (GNU Multiple Precision
                        library, https://gmplib.org/), see >> README.md
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0), shiny
